<h3>22 Dec 2012</h3>
<!-- : story.html,v 1.4 2013/07/08 00:38:55 johnl Exp $ -->
<p><a name="i18neai3"><table width="100%"><tr><td alight=left><b><a href="http://www.jl.ly/Email/i18neai3.html">Making multi-language mail work (Part III)</a></b></a></td>
<td align=right><font size=-1>Email</font></td></tr></table>
<font size="-1"><p>In the
<a href="/Email/i18neai.html">previous</a>
<a href="/Email/i18neai2.html"> installments</a>
we looked at software changes in mail servers, and in
the software that lets user mail programs pick up mail.
What has to change in the user mail programs?</p>

Keeping in mind that I am far from a usability expert
(my ideal interface is a model 33 Teletype), there are
a few things that I can describe without going into the
details of exactly how they would look.
