<h3>22 Jan 2012</h3>
<!-- : story.html,v 1.4 2013/07/08 00:38:55 johnl Exp $ -->
<p><a name="fortigard"><table width="100%"><tr><td alight=left><b><a href="http://www.jl.ly/Email/fortigard.html">No, I'm not offering to tune your spam filters for free</a></b></a></td>
<td align=right><font size=-1>Email</font></td></tr></table>
<font size="-1"><a href="http://www.fortinet.com/solutions/antispam.html">Fortinet</a> is a security
appliance company in California. One of the services they offer to their thousands
of customers is spam filtering, nothing odd about that.
But I was rather startled to see this block at the top of an otherwise ordinary
Russian language spam that arrived here from a poorly secured mail server
in Malaysia
